description.text:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-family: arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;A generic Scattering Power&amp;nbsp;Factorisation&amp;nbsp;Framework for&amp;nbsp;PolSAR&amp;nbsp;data to directly obtain N scattering power components along with a residue power component. Each scattering power component is&amp;nbsp;factorised&amp;nbsp;into similarity using elementary targets and a&amp;nbsp;generalised&amp;nbsp;volume model. The similarity measure relies on a geodesic distance between pairs of 4x4 real&amp;nbsp;Kennaugh&amp;nbsp;matrices. In standard model-based decomposition schemes, the 3x3&amp;nbsp;Hermitian&amp;nbsp;positive semi-definite covariance (or coherency) matrix is expressed as a weighted linear combination of scattering targets following a fixed hierarchical process. In contrast, under the proposed framework, a convex splitting of unity is performed to obtain the weights while preserving the dominance of the scattering components. The product of the total power (Span) with these weights provides the non-negative scattering power components.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
